e, Northumberland, England"},"nl":{"1112–before 1 July 1178":"1112–vóór 1 juli 1178","1112–1178":"1112–1178","1135–1177":"1135–1177","1130–Female":"1130–Overleden","1150–1213":"1150–1213","1082–1166":"1082–1166","1115–Female":"1115–Overleden","1115":"1115","1213":"1213","1135":"1135","1112":"1112","1178":"1178","before 1166":"vóór 1166","1166":"1166","1177":"1177","before 1 July 1178":"vóór 1 juli 1178","1130":"1130","1150":"1150","1082":"1082","Alnwick, Northumberland, England":"Alnwick, Northumberland, England","Shilbottle, Northumberland, England":"Shilbottle, Northumberland, England"},"en":{"1112–before 1 July 1178":"1112–before 1 July 1178","1112–1178":"1112–1178","1135–1177":"1135–1177","1130–Female":"1130–Deceased","1150–1213":"1150–1213","1082–1166":"1082–1166","1115–Female":"1115–Deceased","1115":"1115","1213":"1213","1135":"1135","1112":"1112","1178":"1178","before 1166":"before 1166","1166":"1166","1177":"1177","before 1 July 1178":"before 1 July 1178","1130":"1130","1150":"1150","1082":"1082","Alnwick, Northumberland, England":"Alnwick, Northumberland, England","Shilbottle, Northumberland, England":"Shilbottle, Northumberland, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Tyson","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of <b>Dyson</b> (see   Dye  ).","English: nickname from Old French <i>tison</i> ‘firebrand’, perhaps for someone with a fiery temperament.","Americanized form of German   Theissen   or   Theisen  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dye","meanings":["English (Norfolk): from the Middle English female personal name <i>Dye</i>, a pet form of <i>Denis(e)</i> (from Latin <i>Dionisia</i>); see   Dennis  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Tyson was born in 1112, in Shilbottle, Northumberland, England, his father, Richard Tison, was 30 and his mother, Tyson, was -3. He married Tyson in 1150, in Shilbottle, Northumberland, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died before 1 July 1178, in his hometown."},"et":{"1112–before 1 July 1178":"1112–enne 1. juulit 1178","1112–1178":"1112–1178","1135–1177":"1135–1177","1130–Female":"1130–Surnud","1150–1213":"1150–1213","1082–1166":"1082–1166","1115–Female":"1115–Surnud","1115":"1115","1213":"1213","1135":"1135","1112":"1112","1178":"1178","before 1166":"enne 1166","1166":"1166","1177":"1177","before 1 July 1178":"enne 1. juulit 1178","1130":"1130","1150":"1150","1082":"1082","Alnwick, Northumberland, England":"Alnwick, Northumberland, England","Shilbottle, Northumberland, England":"Shilbottle, Northumberland, England"},"fi":{"1112–before 1 July 1178":"1112–ennen vuotta 1. heinäkuuta 1178","1112–1178":"1112–1178","1135–1177":"1135–1177","1130–Female":"1130–Kuollut","1150–1213":"1150–1213","1082–1166":"1082–1166","1115–Female":"1115–Kuollut","1115":"1115","1213":"1213","1135":"1135","1112":"1112","1178":"1178","before 1166":"ennen vuotta 1166","1166":"1166","1177":"1177","before 1 July 1178":"ennen vuotta 1. heinäkuuta 1178","1130":"1130","1150":"1150","1082":"1082","Alnwick, Northumberland, England":"Alnwick, Northumberland, England","Shilbottle, Northumberland, England":"Shilbottle, Northumberland, England"},"fr":{"1112–before 1 July 1178"